# Implementation Plan: Blink-LLM Pilot & Enterprise Readiness

Blink currently excels at predicting performance for Computer Vision architectures (CNNs, Vision Transformers). This implementation plan outlines the steps to pivot the project to support **Generative AI & Large Language Models (LLMs)** and incorporate **Enterprise Readiness** features like Quantization parsing and CI/CD integration.

## Goal Description
1. **Extend Feature Extraction**: Update [model_analyser.py](file:///c:/Aniket/review%20blink/Neusight/model_analyser.py) to parse standard Hugging Face Transformer parameters (vocab size, hidden dimension, sequence length, attention heads).
2. **KV Cache Modeling**: Implement physically-grounded equations to estimate KV cache memory usage during inference.
3. **Quantization Support**: Add awareness for standard quantization formats (INT8, INT4) predicting how reduced precision affects latency and VRAM footprint.
4. **CI/CD Integration**: Provide a GitHub action/Python script template enabling users to test PRs against latency budgets automatically.

