## Proposed Changes

### Core Extraction & Memory Modeling

#### [MODIFY] [model_analyser.py](file:///c:/Aniket/review%20blink/Neusight/model_analyser.py)
- Update [extract_features](file:///c:/Aniket/review%20blink/Neusight/model_analyser.py#36-127) to detect `transformers.PreTrainedModel` instances.
- Extract `vocab_size`, `hidden_size`, `num_attention_heads`, `num_hidden_layers`, etc.
- In [_estimate_activation_memory_mb](file:///c:/Aniket/review%20blink/Neusight/model_analyser.py#130-172), add an explicit branch for LLMs to compute **KV Cache Memory**:
  ```python
  # Memory scaling for generative decoding
  kv_cache_bytes = 2 * batch_size * seq_len * num_heads * head_dim * bytes_per_param * num_hidden_layers
  ```

#### [MODIFY] [gpu_info.py](file:///c:/Aniket/review%20blink/Neusight/gpu_info.py)
- Incorporate data types (`fp32`, `fp16`, `int8`, `int4`) to dynamically adjust available bandwidth metrics and peak hardware TFLOPS based on tensor core precision levels.

